rComments: Dr. Han is an amazing Prof that really cares about her students and what she teaches! Beware : Take alot of what she says about China with a Grain of Salt she is heavily Biased towards them and to her can do wrong, which is not always the case. Other then that she is super great and I love taking her classes
Dr. Han's HI121 course at the Brantford campus was amazing! She is such a caring teacher, really easy to talk to, and the material itself is interesting and informative. Highly recommend.

Christina Han is one of my favourite professors at Wilfrid Laurier Brantford Campus. She cares about students and is willing to meet outside of office hours if necessary to help you. Interesting lectures, and assigns lots of readings, but gives ample opportunities to succeed in and out of classroom. She is also an extremely kind person. Loved her!
Great prof who is very optimistic and friendly to all.
Great optimistic prof. I like her student-teacher connection. Very clear too.
Shes a friendly, happy approachable professor.
